    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>HONDA EXPANDING IN BRITAIN</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Alan Cowell</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Cowell, Alan</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Japan's Honda Motor Co will expand its British car production capacity to 250,000 a year by 2002; is spending $700 million on expansion, including new plant capable of producing 100,000 cars annually near its existing plant at Swindon (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Bucking a trend among Japanese and other automakers, the Honda Motor Company said it would expand its British car production capacity to 250,000 a year by 2002. Honda is spending $700 million on the expansion, including a new plant capable of producing 100,000 cars annually near its existing factory at Swindon. Nissan and Toyota, along with Ford and BMW, have complained that the strength of the pound against the euro makes their European exports from British plants too expensive.</p>
        <p>Alan Cowell (NYT)</p>
      </block>
